    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle and chop your<strong> smoked streaky</strong> <strong>bacon</strong> roughly</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped bacon</strong> and cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally, until golden and crisp</p><p>Once crisp, transfer to kitchen paper, reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-mushroom-and-leek-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the bacon is cooking, slice your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Wash your <strong>leek[s]</strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat and once hot, add the<strong> sliced mushrooms </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-mushroom-and-leek-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, add your<strong> gluten free spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> spaghetti</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>spaghetti</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-mushroom-and-leek-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms are beginning to soften, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan with the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-7 min or until everything has softened</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min further</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-mushroom-and-leek-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> with your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min further or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy leek & mushroom sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-mushroom-and-leek-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-mushroom-and-leek-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> to the creamy leek & mushroom sauce with a small splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> if needed and cook for 1-2 min further or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy leek & mushroom gluten free spaghetti</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-mushroom-and-leek-gluten-free-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy leek & mushroom gluten free spaghetti</strong> topped with the <strong>grated cheese</strong>, <strong>crispy bacon</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
